    <title>Outline *DELETE BEFORE SUBMISSION*</title>
    <para><emphasis role="bold"><emphasis role="underline">I.
        INTRODUCTION</emphasis></emphasis></para>
    <para>
        <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para><emphasis role="bold"><emphasis role="underline"
                        >Motivation</emphasis></emphasis><itemizedlist>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>HRO Definition, Context</para>
                        </listitem>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Rely on measures, reports, alerts</para>
                        </listitem>
                        <listitem>
                            <para> Measures rely on standardized implementations</para>
                        </listitem>
                        <listitem>
                            <para> However, variation exists in implementations due to various
                                networks, communication channels, set of transformations, and
                                different organizations of clinical data that currently exist.
                            </para>
                        </listitem>
                        <listitem>
                            <para> Part of the problem is expression-logic, part of the problem is
                                terminology. </para>
                            <itemizedlist>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>To assist, there are standards, and DCMs, but variation
                                        exists here in</para>
                                    <itemizedlist>
                                        <listitem>
                                            <para> a) how the data is represented in clinical
                                                statements (INTRO TO CLINICAL STATEMENTS)</para>
                                        </listitem>
                                        <listitem>
                                            <para>b) how the data is entered by end-users in the
                                                structured capture (CLINCAL INPUT FORM) <inlinemediaobject>
                                                  <imageobject>
                                                  <imagedata
                                                  fileref="../../../introduction/src/docbkx/clip_image002_-1458651199.jpg"
                                                  />
                                                  </imageobject>
                                                </inlinemediaobject> &lt;<link
                                                  xlink:href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4141130/"
                                                  >https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4141130/</link>>
                                                  <emphasis>William Goossen: "Detailed Clinical
                                                  Models: Representing Knowledge, Data and Semantics
                                                  in Healthcare Information Technology"
                                                </emphasis></para>
                                        </listitem>
                                    </itemizedlist>
                                </listitem>
                            </itemizedlist>
                        </listitem>
                    </itemizedlist><itemizedlist>
                        <listitem>
                            <para> What we need is a formal, integrated terminology model,
                                post-coordination to minimize complexity in the backend and
                                facilitate better design on front end. </para>
                        </listitem>
                    </itemizedlist></para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para><emphasis role="bold"><emphasis role="underline"
                        >Objectives/Purpose</emphasis></emphasis></para>
                <para> - Therefore, we are proposing ANF. </para>
                <itemizedlist>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Concrete Objectives</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Usage of ANF</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Use cases</para>
                    </listitem>
                </itemizedlist>
                <para> DCM 2010 Ballot as an example:<link
                        xlink:href="http://wiki.hl7.org/index.php?title=Detailed_Clinical_Models"
                    /></para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>
                    <emphasis role="bold"><emphasis role="underline"
                        >Background</emphasis></emphasis>
                </para>
                <para>(Raja did preliminary Lit Review. <emphasis role="bold"><emphasis
                            role="underline">See
                            introduction/src/docbkx/background_refs.xml</emphasis></emphasis>)</para>
                <itemizedlist>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>DCMs </para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>CIMI</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Isosemantic Models</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>HL7v3, CDA, FHIR</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Gaps in existing models and lack of interoperability </para>
                        <para><inlinemediaobject>
                                <imageobject>
                                    <imagedata fileref="images/refcon_comparison%20-%20Copy.jpg"
                                        scale="50"/>
                                </imageobject>
                            </inlinemediaobject></para>
                        <para>Note from Keith: For the ANF document, we should somewhere describe
                            assumptions about what an ANF implementation requires. For example, ANF
                            requires an ability to classify topic expressions (and expressions that
                            may go in other locations). Maybe a section that describes the
                            requirements of a "mapping" based system with a plethora of statement
                            models, and then what ANF requires above and beyond a mapping system,
                            and what the benefits are. </para>
                        <para>Re-using some of the work in the interoperability paper is probably
                            wise. I think a distillation of key concepts should be part of the HL7
                            ballot document. We need to motivate why an ANF approch is necessary as
                            opposed to the status quo.</para>
                    </listitem>
                </itemizedlist>
            </listitem>
        </orderedlist>
    </para>
